  37 bool IsAlwaysTrue(Node* node, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit, ContainerScope* containerScope)
  38 {
  39     std::unique_ptr<Value> value = Evaluate(node, boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetTypeByName(U"bool"), containerScope, boundCompileUnit, true, nullptr, node->GetSpan());
  40     if (value)
  41     {
  42         if (value->GetValueType() == ValueType::boolValue)
  43         {
  44             BoolValue* boolValue = static_cast<BoolValue*>(value.get());
  45             return boolValue->GetValue() == true;
  46         }
  47     }
  48     return false;
  49 }

  51 bool TerminatesFunction(StatementNode* statement, bool inForEverLoop, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit)
  52 {
  53     switch (statement->GetNodeType())
  54     {
  55         case NodeType::compoundStatementNode:
  56         {
  57             CompoundStatementNode* compoundStatement = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(statement);
  58             int n = compoundStatement->Statements().Count();
  59             for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
  60             {
  61                 StatementNode* statement = compoundStatement->Statements()[i];
  62                 if (TerminatesFunction(statement, inForEverLoop, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
  63             }
  64             break;
  65         }
  66         case NodeType::ifStatementNode:
  67         {
  68             IfStatementNode* ifStatement = static_cast<IfStatementNode*>(statement);
  69             if (inForEverLoop || ifStatement->ElseS())
  70             {
  71                 if (TerminatesFunction(ifStatement->ThenS(), inForEverLoop, containerScope, boundCompileUnit) && 
  72                     inForEverLoop || (ifStatement->ElseS() && TerminatesFunction(ifStatement->ElseS(), inForEverLoop, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)))
  73                 {
  74                     return true;
  75                 }
  76             }
  77             break;
  78         }
  79         case NodeType::whileStatementNode:
  80         {
  81             WhileStatementNode* whileStatement = static_cast<WhileStatementNode*>(statement);
  82             if (IsAlwaysTrue(whileStatement->Condition(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope))
  83             {
  84                 if (TerminatesFunction(whileStatement->Statement(), true, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
  85             }
  86             break;
  87         }
  88         case NodeType::doStatementNode:
  89         {
  90             DoStatementNode* doStatement = static_cast<DoStatementNode*>(statement);
  91             if (IsAlwaysTrue(doStatement->Condition(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope))
  92             {
  93                 if (TerminatesFunction(doStatement->Statement(), true, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
  94             }
  95             break;
  96         }
  97         case NodeType::forStatementNode:
  98         {
  99             ForStatementNode* forStatement = static_cast<ForStatementNode*>(statement);
 100             if (!forStatement->Condition() || IsAlwaysTrue(forStatement->Condition(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope))
 101             {
 102                 if (TerminatesFunction(forStatement->ActionS(), true, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return true;
 103             }
 104             break;
 105         }
 106         default:
 107         {
 108             if (statement->IsFunctionTerminatingNode())
 109             {
 110                 return true;
 111             }
 112             break;
 113         }
 114     }
 115     return false;
 116 }
 117 
 118 bool TerminatesCase(StatementNode* statementNode)
 119 {
 120     if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::ifStatementNode)
 121     {
 122         IfStatementNode* ifStatementNode = static_cast<IfStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 123         if (ifStatementNode->ElseS())
 124         {
 125             if (TerminatesCase(ifStatementNode->ThenS()) && TerminatesCase(ifStatementNode->ElseS()))
 126             {
 127                 return true;
 128             }
 129         }
 130     }
 131     else if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
 132     {
 133         CompoundStatementNode* compoundStatement = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 134         int n = compoundStatement->Statements().Count();
 135         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 136         {
 137             StatementNode* statementNode = compoundStatement->Statements()[i];
 138             if (TerminatesCase(statementNode))
 139             {
 140                 return true;
 141             }
 142         }
 143     }
 144     else
 145     {
 146         return statementNode->IsCaseTerminatingNode();
 147     }
 148     return false;
 149 }
 150 
 151 bool TerminatesDefault(StatementNode* statementNode)
 152 {
 153     if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::ifStatementNode)
 154     {
 155         IfStatementNode* ifStatementNode = static_cast<IfStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 156         if (ifStatementNode->ElseS())
 157         {
 158             if (TerminatesDefault(ifStatementNode->ThenS()) && TerminatesDefault(ifStatementNode->ElseS()))
 159             {
 160                 return true;
 161             }
 162         }
 163     }
 164     else if (statementNode->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
 165     {
 166         CompoundStatementNode* compoundStatement = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(statementNode);
 167         int n = compoundStatement->Statements().Count();
 168         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 169         {
 170             StatementNode* statementNode = compoundStatement->Statements()[i];
 171             if (TerminatesDefault(statementNode))
 172             {
 173                 return true;
 174             }
 175         }
 176     }
 177     else
 178     {
 179         return statementNode->IsDefaultTerminatingNode();
 180     }
 181     return false;
 182 }

 186 void CheckFunctionReturnPaths(FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol, FunctionNode& functionNode, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit)
 187 {
 188     CheckFunctionReturnPaths(functionSymbol, functionNode.Body(), functionNode.GetSpan(), containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 189 }
 190 
 191 void CheckFunctionReturnPaths(FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol, CompoundStatementNode* bodyNode, const Span& span, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit)
 192 {
 193     TypeSymbol* returnType = functionSymbol->ReturnType();
 194     if (!returnType || returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::voidTypeSymbol) return;
 195     if (functionSymbol->IsExternal()) return;
 196     if (functionSymbol->IsAbstract()) return;
 197     CompoundStatementNode* body = bodyNode;
 198     if (body)
 199     {
 200         int n = body->Statements().Count();
 201         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 202         {
 203             StatementNode* statement = body->Statements()[i];
 204             if (TerminatesFunction(statement, false, containerScope, boundCompileUnit)) return;
 205         }
 206         throw Exception(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule(), "not all control paths terminate in return or throw statement", span);
 207     }
 208 }

 210 StatementBinder::StatementBinder(BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit_) :
 211     boundCompileUnit(boundCompileUnit_), symbolTable(boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable()), module(&boundCompileUnit.GetModule()), containerScope(nullptr), statement(), compoundLevel(0), insideCatch(false), 
 212     currentClass(nullptr), currentFunction(nullptr), currentStaticConstructorSymbol(nullptr), currentStaticConstructorNode(nullptr), currentConstructorSymbol(nullptr), 
 213     currentConstructorNode(nullptr), currentDestructorSymbol(nullptr), currentDestructorNode(nullptr), currentMemberFunctionSymbol(nullptr), currentMemberFunctionNode(nullptr), 
 214     switchConditionType(nullptr), currentCaseValueMap(nullptr), currentGotoCaseStatements(nullptr), currentGotoDefaultStatements(nullptr), postfix(false), compilingThrow(false), 
 215     compilingReleaseExceptionStatement(false)
 216 {
 217 }

 224 void StatementBinder::Visit(NamespaceNode& namespaceNode)
 225 {
 226     std::unique_ptr<BoundNamespace> ns(new BoundNamespace(module, namespaceNode));
 227     boundCompileUnit.PushNamespace(ns.get());
 228     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 229     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&namespaceNode);
 230     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 231     int n = namespaceNode.Members().Count();
 232     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 233     {
 234         Node* member = namespaceNode.Members()[i];
 235         member->Accept(*this);
 236     }
 237     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 238     boundCompileUnit.PopNamespace();
 239     boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(     std::unique_ptr<BoundNode>(ns.release()));
 240 }

 242 void StatementBinder::Visit(EnumTypeNode& enumTypeNode)
 243 {
 244     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&enumTypeNode);
 245     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::enumTypeSymbol, "enum type symbols expected");
 246     EnumTypeSymbol* enumTypeSymbol = static_cast<EnumTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 247     std::unique_ptr<BoundEnumTypeDefinition> boundEnum(new BoundEnumTypeDefinition(module, enumTypeSymbol));
 248     boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundEnum));
 249 }

 251 void StatementBinder::Visit(ClassNode& classNode)
 252 {
 253     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 254     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&classNode);
 255     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTypeSymbol || symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classTemplateSpecializationSymbol, "class type symbol expected");
 256     ClassTypeSymbol* classTypeSymbol = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(symbol);
 257     if (classTypeSymbol->IsClassTemplate())
 258     {
 259         return;
 260     }
 261     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 262     std::unique_ptr<BoundClass> boundClass(new BoundClass(module, classTypeSymbol));
 263     BoundClass* prevClass = currentClass;
 264     currentClass = boundClass.get();
 265     int n = classNode.Members().Count();
 266     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 267     {
 268         Node* classMember = classNode.Members()[i];
 269         classMember->Accept(*this);
 270     }
 271     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(classNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 272     boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundClass));
 273     DestructorSymbol* destructorSymbol = classTypeSymbol->Destructor();
 274     if (destructorSymbol && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::info))
 275     {
 276         Node* node = symbolTable.GetNodeNoThrow(destructorSymbol);
 277         if (!node)
 278         {
 279             GenerateDestructorImplementation(currentClass, destructorSymbol, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, currentFunction, classNode.GetSpan());
 280         }
 281     }
 282     currentClass = prevClass;
 283     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 284 }

 286 void StatementBinder::Visit(FunctionNode& functionNode)
 287 {
 288     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 289     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&functionNode);
 290     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::functionSymbol, "function symbol expected");
 291     FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol = static_cast<FunctionSymbol*>(symbol);
 292     if (functionSymbol->IsFunctionTemplate())
 293     {
 294         return;
 295     }
 296     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 297     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(module, functionSymbol));
 298     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 299     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 300     if (functionNode.Body())
 301     {
 302         compoundLevel = 0;
 303         functionNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 304         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 305         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 306         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 307         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 308         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(functionSymbol, functionNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 309         boundCompileUnit.AddBoundNode(std::move(boundFunction));
 310     }
 311     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(functionNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 312     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 313     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 314 }

 316 void StatementBinder::Visit(StaticConstructorNode& staticConstructorNode)
 317 {
 318     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 319     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&staticConstructorNode);
 320     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::staticConstructorSymbol,  "static constructor symbol expected");
 321     StaticConstructorSymbol* staticConstructorSymbol = static_cast<StaticConstructorSymbol*>(symbol);
 322     StaticConstructorSymbol* prevStaticConstructorSymbol = currentStaticConstructorSymbol;
 323     currentStaticConstructorSymbol = staticConstructorSymbol;
 324     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 325     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(module, staticConstructorSymbol));
 326     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 327     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 328     if (staticConstructorNode.Body())
 329     {
 330         StaticConstructorNode* prevStaticConstructorNode = currentStaticConstructorNode;
 331         currentStaticConstructorNode = &staticConstructorNode;
 332         compoundLevel = 0;
 333         staticConstructorNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 334         currentStaticConstructorNode = prevStaticConstructorNode;
 335         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 336         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 337         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 338         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 339         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(staticConstructorSymbol, staticConstructorNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 340         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 341     }
 342     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(staticConstructorNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 343     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 344     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 345     currentStaticConstructorSymbol = prevStaticConstructorSymbol;
 346 }

 348 void StatementBinder::Visit(ConstructorNode& constructorNode)
 349 {
 350     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 351     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&constructorNode);
 352     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::constructorSymbol, "constructor symbol expected");
 353     ConstructorSymbol* constructorSymbol = static_cast<ConstructorSymbol*>(symbol);
 354     ConstructorSymbol* prevConstructorSymbol = currentConstructorSymbol;
 355     currentConstructorSymbol = constructorSymbol;
 356     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 357     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(module, constructorSymbol));
 358     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 359     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 360     if (constructorNode.Body())
 361     {
 362         ConstructorNode* prevConstructorNode = currentConstructorNode;
 363         currentConstructorNode = &constructorNode;
 364         compoundLevel = 0;
 365         constructorNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 366         currentConstructorNode = prevConstructorNode;
 367         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 368         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 369         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 370         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 371     }
 372     else if (constructorSymbol->IsDefault())
 373     {
 374         ConstructorNode* prevConstructorNode = currentConstructorNode;
 375         currentConstructorNode = &constructorNode;
 376         std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement> boundCompoundStatement(new BoundCompoundStatement(module, constructorNode.GetSpan()));
 377         GenerateClassInitialization(currentConstructorSymbol, currentConstructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, true, constructorNode.GetSpan());
 378         currentConstructorNode = prevConstructorNode;
 379         boundFunction->SetBody(std::move(boundCompoundStatement));
 380     }
 381     if (boundFunction->Body())
 382     {
 383         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(constructorSymbol, constructorNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 384         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 385     }
 386     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(constructorNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 387     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 388     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 389     currentConstructorSymbol = prevConstructorSymbol;
 390 }

 392 void StatementBinder::Visit(DestructorNode& destructorNode)
 393 {
 394     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 395     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&destructorNode);
 396     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::destructorSymbol, "destructor symbol expected");
 397     DestructorSymbol* destructorSymbol = static_cast<DestructorSymbol*>(symbol);
 398     DestructorSymbol* prevDestructorSymbol = currentDestructorSymbol;
 399     currentDestructorSymbol = destructorSymbol;
 400     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 401     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(module, destructorSymbol));
 402     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 403     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 404     if (destructorNode.Body())
 405     {
 406         DestructorNode* prevDestructorNode = currentDestructorNode;
 407         currentDestructorNode = &destructorNode;
 408         compoundLevel = 0;
 409         destructorNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 410         currentDestructorNode = prevDestructorNode;
 411         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 412         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 413         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 414         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 415     }
 416     else if (destructorSymbol->IsDefault())
 417     {
 418         DestructorNode* prevDestructorNode = currentDestructorNode;
 419         currentDestructorNode = &destructorNode;
 420         std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement> boundCompoundStatement(new BoundCompoundStatement(module, destructorNode.GetSpan()));
 421         GenerateClassTermination(currentDestructorSymbol, currentDestructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, currentDestructorNode->GetSpan());
 422         currentDestructorNode = prevDestructorNode;
 423         boundFunction->SetBody(std::move(boundCompoundStatement));
 424     }
 425     if (boundFunction->Body())
 426     {
 427         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(destructorSymbol, destructorNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 428         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 429     }
 430     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(destructorNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 431     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 432     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 433     currentDestructorSymbol = prevDestructorSymbol;
 434 }

 436 void StatementBinder::Visit(MemberFunctionNode& memberFunctionNode)
 437 {
 438     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 439     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&memberFunctionNode);
 440     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::memberFunctionSymbol, "member function symbol expected");
 441     MemberFunctionSymbol* memberFunctionSymbol = static_cast<MemberFunctionSymbol*>(symbol);
 442     MemberFunctionSymbol* prevMemberFunctionSymbol = currentMemberFunctionSymbol;
 443     currentMemberFunctionSymbol = memberFunctionSymbol;
 444     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 445     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(module, memberFunctionSymbol));
 446     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 447     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 448     if (memberFunctionNode.Body())
 449     {
 450         MemberFunctionNode* prevMemberFunctionNode = currentMemberFunctionNode;
 451         currentMemberFunctionNode = &memberFunctionNode;
 452         compoundLevel = 0;
 453         memberFunctionNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 454         currentMemberFunctionNode = prevMemberFunctionNode;
 455         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 456         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 457         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 458         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 459     }
 460     else if (memberFunctionSymbol->IsDefault())
 461     {
 462         Assert(memberFunctionSymbol->GroupName() == U"operator=", "operator= expected");
 463         MemberFunctionNode* prevMemberFunctionNode = currentMemberFunctionNode;
 464         currentMemberFunctionNode = &memberFunctionNode;
 465         std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement> boundCompoundStatement(new BoundCompoundStatement(module, memberFunctionNode.GetSpan()));
 466         GenerateClassAssignment(currentMemberFunctionSymbol, currentMemberFunctionNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, true, memberFunctionNode.GetSpan());
 467         currentMemberFunctionNode = prevMemberFunctionNode;
 468         boundFunction->SetBody(std::move(boundCompoundStatement));
 469     }
 470     if (boundFunction->Body())
 471     {
 472         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(memberFunctionSymbol, memberFunctionNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 473         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 474     }
 475     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(memberFunctionNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 476     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 477     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 478     currentMemberFunctionSymbol = prevMemberFunctionSymbol;
 479 }
 480 
 481 void StatementBinder::Visit(ConversionFunctionNode& conversionFunctionNode)
 482 {
 483     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 484     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&conversionFunctionNode);
 485     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::conversionFunctionSymbol, "conversion function symbol expected");
 486     ConversionFunctionSymbol* conversionFunctionSymbol = static_cast<ConversionFunctionSymbol*>(symbol);
 487     containerScope = symbol->GetContainerScope();
 488     std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(module, conversionFunctionSymbol));
 489     BoundFunction* prevFunction = currentFunction;
 490     currentFunction = boundFunction.get();
 491     if (conversionFunctionNode.Body())
 492     {
 493         compoundLevel = 0;
 494         conversionFunctionNode.Body()->Accept(*this);
 495         BoundStatement* boundStatement = statement.release();
 496         Assert(boundStatement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCompoundStatement, "bound compound statement expected");
 497         BoundCompoundStatement* compoundStatement = static_cast<BoundCompoundStatement*>(boundStatement);
 498         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(compoundStatement));
 499         CheckFunctionReturnPaths(conversionFunctionSymbol, conversionFunctionNode, containerScope, boundCompileUnit);
 500         currentClass->AddMember(std::move(boundFunction));
 501     }
 502     boundCompileUnit.GetAttributeBinder()->GenerateImplementation(conversionFunctionNode.GetAttributes(), symbol, this);
 503     currentFunction = prevFunction;
 504     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 505 }
 506 
 507 void StatementBinder::Visit(CompoundStatementNode& compoundStatementNode)
 508 {
 509     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 510     Symbol* symbol = symbolTable.GetSymbol(&compoundStatementNode);
 511     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::declarationBlock, "declaration block expected");
 512     DeclarationBlock* declarationBlock = static_cast<DeclarationBlock*>(symbol);
 513     containerScope = declarationBlock->GetContainerScope();
 514     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement> boundCompoundStatement(new BoundCompoundStatement(module, compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), compoundStatementNode.EndBraceSpan()));
 515     if (compoundLevel == 0)
 516     {
 517         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::profile))
 518         {
 519             bool profile = true;
 520             if (currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->IsProgramMain())
 521             {
 522                 profile = false;
 523             }
 524             else if (currentClass && currentClass->GetClassTypeSymbol()->FullName() == U"System.Runtime.FunctionProfiler")
 525             {
 526                 profile = false;
 527             }
 528             if (profile)
 529             {
 530                 boost::uuids::uuid functionId = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->FunctionId();
 531                 symbolTable.MapProfiledFunction(functionId, currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->FullName());
 532                 ConstructionStatementNode constructFunctionProfiler(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), new IdentifierNode(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"System.Runtime.FunctionProfiler"), 
 533                     new IdentifierNode(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"@functionProfiler"));
 534                 constructFunctionProfiler.AddArgument(new UuidLiteralNode(compoundStatementNode.GetSpan(), functionId));
 535                 symbolTable.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
 536                 symbolTable.BeginContainer(containerScope->Container());
 537                 SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreatorVisitor(symbolTable);
 538                 constructFunctionProfiler.Accept(symbolCreatorVisitor);
 539                 symbolTable.EndContainer();
 540                 TypeBinder typeBinder(boundCompileUnit);
 541                 typeBinder.SetContainerScope(containerScope);
 542                 typeBinder.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
 543                 constructFunctionProfiler.Accept(typeBinder);
 544                 constructFunctionProfiler.Accept(*this);
 545                 boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(ReleaseStatement()));
 546             }
 547         }
 548         if (currentStaticConstructorSymbol && currentStaticConstructorNode)
 549         {
 550             GenerateStaticClassInitialization(currentStaticConstructorSymbol, currentStaticConstructorNode, boundCompileUnit, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, containerScope, this, 
 551                 boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan());
 552         }
 553         else if (currentConstructorSymbol && currentConstructorNode)
 554         {
 555             GenerateClassInitialization(currentConstructorSymbol, currentConstructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, false, 
 556                 boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan());
 557         }
 558         else if (currentMemberFunctionSymbol && currentMemberFunctionSymbol->GroupName() == U"operator=" && currentMemberFunctionNode)
 559         {
 560             GenerateClassAssignment(currentMemberFunctionSymbol, currentMemberFunctionNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, false, 
 561                 boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan());
 562         }
 563         else if (currentMemberFunctionSymbol && currentMemberFunctionSymbol->IsStatic() && currentMemberFunctionNode)
 564         {
 565             if (currentClass->GetClassTypeSymbol()->StaticConstructor())
 566             {
 567                 boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(
 568                     new BoundFunctionCall(module, boundCompoundStatement->GetSpan(), currentClass->GetClassTypeSymbol()->StaticConstructor())))));
 569             }
 570         }
 571     }
 572     ++compoundLevel;
 573     int n = compoundStatementNode.Statements().Count();
 574     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 575     {
 576         StatementNode* statementNode = compoundStatementNode.Statements()[i];
 577         statementNode->Accept(*this);
 578         boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(std::move(statement));
 579     }
 580     --compoundLevel;
 581     if (compoundLevel == 0 && currentDestructorSymbol && currentDestructorNode)
 582     {
 583         GenerateClassTermination(currentDestructorSymbol, currentDestructorNode, boundCompoundStatement.get(), currentFunction, boundCompileUnit, containerScope, this, boundCompoundStatement->EndSpan());
 584     }
 585     AddStatement(boundCompoundStatement.release());
 586     if (compoundStatementNode.Label())
 587     {
 588         statement->SetLabel(compoundStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 589     }
 590     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 591 }
 592 
 593 void StatementBinder::Visit(ReturnStatementNode& returnStatementNode)
 594 {
 595     if (returnStatementNode.Expression())
 596     {
 597         if (currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnsClassInterfaceOrClassDelegateByValue())
 598         {
 599             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> classReturnLookups;
 600             classReturnLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 601             classReturnLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType()->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
 602             classReturnLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 603             std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> classReturnArgs;
 604             classReturnArgs.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnParam())));
 605             TypeSymbol* returnType = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 606             bool returnClassDelegateType = returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classDelegateTypeSymbol;
 607             std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> expression = BindExpression(returnStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this, false, returnClassDelegateType, 
 608                 returnClassDelegateType);
 609             bool exceptionCapture = false;
 610             if (insideCatch && expression->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 611             {
 612                 exceptionCapture = true;
 613             }
 614             if (expression->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundLocalVariable)
 615             {
 616                 std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> rvalueLookups;
 617                 rvalueLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 618                 rvalueLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 619                 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> rvalueArguments;
 620                 if (returnClassDelegateType && expression->GetType()->BaseType()->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::functionGroupTypeSymbol)
 621                 {
 622                     TypeSymbol* exprType = expression->GetType();
 623                     ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
 624                     expression.reset(new BoundConversion(module, std::move(expression), boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(exprType, returnType, containerScope, currentFunction, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), argumentMatch)));
 625                 }
 626                 rvalueArguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
 627                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> rvalueExpr = ResolveOverload(U"System.Rvalue", containerScope, rvalueLookups, rvalueArguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
 628                     returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 629                 expression = std::move(rvalueExpr);
 630             }
 631             classReturnArgs.push_back(std::move(expression));
 632             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> constructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, classReturnLookups, classReturnArgs, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
 633                 returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 634             std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> constructStatement(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::move(constructorCall)));
 635             AddStatement(constructStatement.release());
 636             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> returnFunctionCall;
 637             std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> returnStatement(new BoundReturnStatement(module, std::move(returnFunctionCall), returnStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 638             if (exceptionCapture)
 639             {
 640                 AddReleaseExceptionStatement(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 641             }
 642             AddStatement(returnStatement.release());
 643         }
 644         else
 645         {
 646             TypeSymbol* returnType = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 647             bool returnDelegateType = false;
 648             bool returnClassDelegateType = false;
 649             bool exceptionCapture = false;
 650             if (returnType)
 651             {
 652                 returnDelegateType = returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::delegateTypeSymbol;
 653                 returnClassDelegateType = returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::classDelegateTypeSymbol;
 654             }
 655             if (returnType && returnType->GetSymbolType() != SymbolType::voidTypeSymbol)
 656             {
 657                 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> returnTypeArgs;
 658                 BoundTypeExpression* boundTypeExpression = new BoundTypeExpression(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), returnType);
 659                 returnTypeArgs.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundTypeExpression>(boundTypeExpression));
 660                 std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> functionScopeLookups;
 661                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
 662                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, returnType->BaseType()->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
 663                 functionScopeLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
 664                 std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> returnFunctionCall = ResolveOverload(U"@return", containerScope, functionScopeLookups, returnTypeArgs, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
 665                     returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 666                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> expression = BindExpression(returnStatementNode.Expression(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this, false, 
 667                     returnDelegateType || returnClassDelegateType, returnClassDelegateType);
 668                 if (insideCatch && expression->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 669                 {
 670                     exceptionCapture = true;
 671                 }
 672                 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> returnValueArguments;
 673                 returnValueArguments.push_back(std::move(expression));
 674                 FunctionMatch functionMatch(returnFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
 675                 bool conversionFound = FindConversions(boundCompileUnit, returnFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol(), returnValueArguments, functionMatch, ConversionType::implicit_, 
 676                     containerScope, currentFunction, returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 677                 if (conversionFound)
 678                 {
 679                     Assert(!functionMatch.argumentMatches.empty(), "argument match expected");
 680                     ArgumentMatch argumentMatch = functionMatch.argumentMatches[0];
 681                     if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags != OperationFlags::none)
 682                     {
 683                         if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::addr)
 684                         {
 685                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->AddLvalueReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 686                             BoundAddressOfExpression* addressOfExpression = new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 687                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(addressOfExpression);
 688                         }
 689                         else if (argumentMatch.preReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::deref)
 690                         {
 691                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 692                             BoundDereferenceExpression* dereferenceExpression = new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 693                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(dereferenceExpression);
 694                         }
 695                     }
 696                     FunctionSymbol* conversionFun = argumentMatch.conversionFun;
 697                     if (conversionFun)
 698                     {
 699                         if (conversionFun->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::constructorSymbol)
 700                         {
 701                             BoundFunctionCall* constructorCall = new BoundFunctionCall(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), conversionFun);
 702                             LocalVariableSymbol* temporary = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->CreateTemporary(conversionFun->ConversionTargetType(), returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 703                             constructorCall->AddArgument(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), temporary)), 
 704                                 conversionFun->ConversionTargetType()->AddPointer(returnStatementNode.GetSpan()))));
 705                             constructorCall->AddArgument(std::move(returnValueArguments[0]));
 706                             BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression* conversion = new BoundConstructAndReturnTemporaryExpression(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(constructorCall), 
 707                                      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLocalVariable(module, returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), temporary)));
 708                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(conversion);
 709                         }
 710                         else
 711                         {
 712                             BoundConversion* boundConversion = new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(returnValueArguments[0].release()), conversionFun);
 713                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(boundConversion);
 714                         }
 715                     }
 716                     if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags != OperationFlags::none)
 717                     {
 718                         if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::addr)
 719                         {
 720                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->AddLvalueReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 721                             BoundAddressOfExpression* addressOfExpression = new BoundAddressOfExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 722                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(addressOfExpression);
 723                         }
 724                         else if (argumentMatch.postReferenceConversionFlags == OperationFlags::deref)
 725                         {
 726                             TypeSymbol* type = returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->RemoveReference(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 727                             BoundDereferenceExpression* dereferenceExpression = new BoundDereferenceExpression(module, std::move(returnValueArguments[0]), type);
 728                             returnValueArguments[0].reset(dereferenceExpression);
 729                         }
 730                     }
 731                     returnFunctionCall->SetArguments(std::move(returnValueArguments));
 732                 }
 733                 else
 734                 {
 735                     throw Exception(module, "no implicit conversion from '" + ToUtf8(returnValueArguments[0]->GetType()->FullName()) + "' to '" + ToUtf8(returnType->FullName()) + "' exists", 
 736                         returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 737                 }
 738                 CheckAccess(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol(), returnFunctionCall->GetFunctionSymbol());
 739                 if (exceptionCapture)
 740                 {
 741                     AddReleaseExceptionStatement(returnStatementNode.GetSpan());
 742                 }
 743                 AddStatement(new BoundReturnStatement(module, std::move(returnFunctionCall), returnStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 744             }
 745             else
 746             {
 747                 if (returnType)
 748                 {
 749                     throw Exception(module, "void function cannot return a value", returnStatementNode.Expression()->GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 750                 }
 751                 else
 752                 {
 753                     throw Exception(module, "constructor or assignment function cannot return a value", returnStatementNode.Expression()->GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 754                 }
 755             }
 756         }
 757     }
 758     else
 759     {
 760         TypeSymbol* returnType = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->ReturnType();
 761         if (!returnType || returnType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::voidTypeSymbol)
 762         {
 763             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> returnFunctionCall;
 764             AddStatement(new BoundReturnStatement(module, std::move(returnFunctionCall), returnStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 765         }
 766         else
 767         {
 768             throw Exception(module, "nonvoid function must return a value", returnStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
 769         }
 770     }
 771     if (returnStatementNode.Label())
 772     {
 773         statement->SetLabel(returnStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 774     }
 775 }
 776 
 777 void StatementBinder::Visit(IfStatementNode& ifStatementNode)
 778 {
 779     bool exceptionCapture = false;
 780     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition = BindExpression(ifStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
 781     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 782     {
 783         exceptionCapture = true;
 784     }
 785     if (!TypesEqual(symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"bool"), condition->GetType()->PlainType(ifStatementNode.GetSpan())))
 786     {
 787         throw Exception(module, "condition of an if statement must be a Boolean expression", ifStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
 788     }
 789     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> s;
 790     if (statement)
 791     {
 792         s = std::move(statement);
 793     }
 794     ifStatementNode.ThenS()->Accept(*this);
 795     BoundStatement* thenS = statement.release();
 796     BoundStatement* elseS = nullptr;
 797     if (ifStatementNode.ElseS())
 798     {
 799         ifStatementNode.ElseS()->Accept(*this);
 800         elseS = statement.release();
 801     }
 802     if (s)
 803     {
 804         AddStatement(s.release());
 805     }
 806     if (exceptionCapture)
 807     {
 808         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(ifStatementNode.GetSpan());
 809     }
 810     AddStatement(new BoundIfStatement(module, ifStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::move(condition),      std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(thenS), std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(elseS)));
 811     if (ifStatementNode.Label())
 812     {
 813         statement->SetLabel(ifStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 814     }
 815 }
 816 
 817 void StatementBinder::Visit(WhileStatementNode& whileStatementNode)
 818 {
 819     bool exceptionCapture = false;
 820     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition = BindExpression(whileStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
 821     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 822     {
 823         exceptionCapture = true;
 824     }
 825     if (!TypesEqual(symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"bool"), condition->GetType()->PlainType(whileStatementNode.GetSpan())))
 826     {
 827         throw Exception(module, "condition of a while statement must be a Boolean expression", whileStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
 828     }
 829     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> s;
 830     if (statement)
 831     {
 832         s = std::move(statement);
 833     }
 834     whileStatementNode.Statement()->Accept(*this);
 835     BoundStatement* stmt = statement.release();
 836     if (s)
 837     {
 838         AddStatement(s.release());
 839     }
 840     if (exceptionCapture)
 841     {
 842         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(whileStatementNode.GetSpan());
 843     }
 844     AddStatement(new BoundWhileStatement(module, whileStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::move(condition),      std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(stmt)));
 845     if (whileStatementNode.Label())
 846     {
 847         statement->SetLabel(whileStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 848     }
 849 }

 851 void StatementBinder::Visit(DoStatementNode& doStatementNode)
 852 {
 853     bool exceptionCapture = false;
 854     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition = BindExpression(doStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
 855     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 856     {
 857         exceptionCapture = true;
 858     }
 859     if (!TypesEqual(symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"bool"), condition->GetType()->PlainType(doStatementNode.GetSpan())))
 860     {
 861         throw Exception(module, "condition of a do statement must be a Boolean expression", doStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
 862     }
 863     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> s;
 864     if (statement)
 865     {
 866         s = std::move(statement);
 867     }
 868     doStatementNode.Statement()->Accept(*this);
 869     BoundStatement* stmt = statement.release();
 870     if (s)
 871     {
 872         AddStatement(s.release());
 873     }
 874     if (exceptionCapture)
 875     {
 876         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(doStatementNode.GetSpan());
 877     }
 878     AddStatement(new BoundDoStatement(module, doStatementNode.GetSpan(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(stmt), std::move(condition)));
 879     if (doStatementNode.Label())
 880     {
 881         statement->SetLabel(doStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 882     }

 884 
 885 void StatementBinder::Visit(ForStatementNode& forStatementNode)
 886 {
 887     ContainerScope* prevContainerScope = containerScope;
 888     Symbol* symbol = boundCompileUnit.GetSymbolTable().GetSymbol(&forStatementNode);
 889     Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::declarationBlock, "declaration block expected");
 890     DeclarationBlock* declarationBlock = static_cast<DeclarationBlock*>(symbol);
 891     containerScope = declarationBlock->GetContainerScope();
 892     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition;
 893     if (forStatementNode.Condition())
 894     {
 895         condition = BindExpression(forStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
 896     }
 897     else
 898     {
 899         BooleanLiteralNode trueNode(forStatementNode.GetSpan(), true);
 900         condition = BindExpression(&trueNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
 901     }
 902     bool exceptionCapture = false;
 903     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
 904     {
 905         exceptionCapture = true;
 906     }
 907     if (!TypesEqual(symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"bool"), condition->GetType()->PlainType(forStatementNode.GetSpan())))
 908     {
 909         throw Exception(module, "condition of a for statement must be a Boolean expression", forStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
 910     }
 911     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> s;
 912     if (statement)
 913     {
 914         s = std::move(statement);
 915     }
 916     forStatementNode.InitS()->Accept(*this);
 917     BoundStatement* initS = statement.release();
 918     forStatementNode.LoopS()->Accept(*this);
 919     BoundStatement* loopS = statement.release();
 920     forStatementNode.ActionS()->Accept(*this);
 921     BoundStatement* actionS = statement.release();
 922     if (s)
 923     {
 924         AddStatement(s.release());
 925     }
 926     if (exceptionCapture)
 927     {
 928         AddReleaseExceptionStatement(forStatementNode.GetSpan());
 929     }
 930     AddStatement(new BoundForStatement(module, forStatementNode.GetSpan(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(initS), std::move(condition), std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(loopS), 
 931              std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(actionS)));
 932     if (forStatementNode.Label())
 933     {
 934         statement->SetLabel(forStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 935     }
 936     containerScope = prevContainerScope;
 937 }

 939 void StatementBinder::Visit(BreakStatementNode& breakStatementNode)
 940 {
 941     const Node* parent = breakStatementNode.Parent();
 942     const StatementNode* parentStatement = nullptr;
 943     if (parent && parent->IsStatementNode())
 944     {
 945         parentStatement = static_cast<const StatementNode*>(parent);
 946     }
 947     while (parentStatement && !parentStatement->IsBreakEnclosingStatementNode())
 948     {
 949         parent = parentStatement->Parent();
 950         if (parent && parent->IsStatementNode())
 951         {
 952             parentStatement = static_cast<const StatementNode*>(parent);
 953         }
 954         else
 955         {
 956             parentStatement = nullptr;
 957         }
 958     }
 959     if (!parentStatement)
 960     {
 961         throw Exception(module, "break statement must be enclosed in a while, do, for or switch statement", breakStatementNode.GetSpan());
 962     }
 963     AddStatement(new BoundBreakStatement(module, breakStatementNode.GetSpan()));
 964     if (breakStatementNode.Label())
 965     {
 966         statement->SetLabel(breakStatementNode.Label()->Label());
 967     }
 968 }

1236 TypeExpr* typeExprGrammar = nullptr;
1237 
1238 void StatementBinder::Visit(RangeForStatementNode& rangeForStatementNode)
1239 {
1240     const Span& span = rangeForStatementNode.GetSpan();
1241     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> container = BindExpression(rangeForStatementNode.Container(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1242     TypeSymbol* plainContainerType = container->GetType()->PlainType(span);

1244     if (!typeExprGrammar)

1247     }
1248     ParsingContext parsingContext;
1249     std::unique_ptr<Node> containerTypeNode(typeExprGrammar->Parse(&plainContainerTypeFullName[0], &plainContainerTypeFullName[plainContainerTypeFullName.length()], 0, "", &parsingContext));
1250     std::unique_ptr<IdentifierNode> iteratorTypeNode = nullptr;
1251     if (container->GetType()->IsConstType())
1252     {
1253         iteratorTypeNode.reset(new IdentifierNode(span, U"ConstIterator"));
1254     }
1255     else
1256     {
1257         iteratorTypeNode.reset(new IdentifierNode(span, U"Iterator"));
1258     }
1259     CloneContext cloneContext;
1260     std::unique_ptr<CompoundStatementNode> compoundStatementNode(new CompoundStatementNode(span));
1261     if (rangeForStatementNode.Action()->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
1262     {
1263         CompoundStatementNode* action = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Action());
1264         compoundStatementNode->SetEndBraceSpan(action->EndBraceSpan());
1265     }
1266     else
1267     {
1268         compoundStatementNode->SetEndBraceSpan(span);
1269     }
1270     compoundStatementNode->SetParent(rangeForStatementNode.Parent());
1271     ConstructionStatementNode* constructEndIteratorStatement = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, 
1272         new DotNode(span, containerTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(iteratorTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext))), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@end"));
1273     if (container->GetType()->IsConstType())
1274     {
1275         constructEndIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"CEnd"))));
1276     }
1277     else
1278     {
1279         constructEndIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"End"))));
1280     }
1281     compoundStatementNode->AddStatement(constructEndIteratorStatement);
1282     ConstructionStatementNode* constructIteratorStatement = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, 
1283         new DotNode(span, containerTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(iteratorTypeNode->Clone(cloneContext))), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@it"));
1284     if (container->GetType()->IsConstType())
1285     {
1286         constructIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"CBegin"))));
1287     }
1288     else
1289     {
1290         constructIteratorStatement->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, rangeForStatementNode.Container()->Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"Begin"))));
1291     }
1292     Node* itNotEndCond = new NotEqualNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@it"), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@end"));
1293     StatementNode* incrementItStatement = new ExpressionStatementNode(span, new PrefixIncrementNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@it")));
1294     CompoundStatementNode* actionStatement = new CompoundStatementNode(span);
1295     if (rangeForStatementNode.Action()->GetNodeType() == NodeType::compoundStatementNode)
1296     {
1297         CompoundStatementNode* action = static_cast<CompoundStatementNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Action());
1298         actionStatement->SetEndBraceSpan(action->EndBraceSpan());
1299     }
1300     else
1301     {
1302         actionStatement->SetEndBraceSpan(span);
1303     }
1304     ConstructionStatementNode* constructLoopVarStatement = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, 
1305         rangeForStatementNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Id()->Clone(cloneContext)));
1306     constructLoopVarStatement->AddArgument(new DerefNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@it")));
1307     actionStatement->AddStatement(constructLoopVarStatement);
1308     actionStatement->AddStatement(static_cast<StatementNode*>(rangeForStatementNode.Action()->Clone(cloneContext)));
1309     ForStatementNode* forStatement = new ForStatementNode(span, constructIteratorStatement, itNotEndCond, incrementItStatement, actionStatement);
1310     compoundStatementNode->AddStatement(forStatement);
1311 
1312     symbolTable.BeginContainer(containerScope->Container());
1313     SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreatorVisitor(symbolTable);
1314     compoundStatementNode->Accept(symbolCreatorVisitor);
1315     symbolTable.EndContainer();
1316     TypeBinder typeBinder(boundCompileUnit);
1317     typeBinder.SetContainerScope(containerScope);
1318     typeBinder.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
1319     compoundStatementNode->Accept(typeBinder);
1320     compoundStatementNode->Accept(*this);

1323 void StatementBinder::Visit(SwitchStatementNode& switchStatementNode)

1326     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> condition = BindExpression(switchStatementNode.Condition(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1327     if (insideCatch && condition->ContainsExceptionCapture())
1328     {
1329         exceptionCapture = true;
1330     }
1331     TypeSymbol* conditionType = condition->GetType();
1332     if (conditionType->IsSwitchConditionType())
1333     {
1334         if (conditionType->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::enumTypeSymbol)
1335         {
1336             EnumTypeSymbol* enumType = static_cast<EnumTypeSymbol*>(conditionType);
1337             conditionType = enumType->UnderlyingType();
1338         }
1339         TypeSymbol* prevSwitchConditionType = switchConditionType;
1340         switchConditionType = conditionType;
1341         std::unordered_map<IntegralValue, CaseStatementNode*, IntegralValueHash>* prevCaseValueMap = currentCaseValueMap;
1342         std::unordered_map<IntegralValue, CaseStatementNode*, IntegralValueHash> caseValueMap;
1343         currentCaseValueMap = &caseValueMap;
1344         std::vector<std::pair<BoundGotoCaseStatement*, IntegralValue>>* prevGotoCaseStatements = currentGotoCaseStatements;
1345         std::vector<std::pair<BoundGotoCaseStatement*, IntegralValue>> gotoCaseStatements;
1346         currentGotoCaseStatements = &gotoCaseStatements;
1347         std::vector<BoundGotoDefaultStatement*>* prevGotoDefaultStatements = currentGotoDefaultStatements;
1348         std::vector<BoundGotoDefaultStatement*> gotoDefaultStatements;
1349         currentGotoDefaultStatements = &gotoDefaultStatements;
1350         std::unique_ptr<BoundSwitchStatement> boundSwitchStatement(new BoundSwitchStatement(module, switchStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::move(condition)));
1351         int n = switchStatementNode.Cases().Count();
1352         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1353         {
1354             CaseStatementNode* caseS = switchStatementNode.Cases()[i];
1355             caseS->Accept(*this);
1356             Assert(statement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundCaseStatement, "case statement expected");
1357             boundSwitchStatement->AddCaseStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCaseStatement>(static_cast<BoundCaseStatement*>(statement.release())));
1358         }
1359         if (switchStatementNode.Default())
1360         {
1361             switchStatementNode.Default()->Accept(*this);
1362             Assert(statement->GetBoundNodeType() == BoundNodeType::boundDefaultStatement, "default statement expected");
1363             boundSwitchStatement->SetDefaultStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundDefaultStatement>(static_cast<BoundDefaultStatement*>(statement.release())));
1364         }
1365         for (const std::pair<BoundGotoCaseStatement*, IntegralValue>& p : gotoCaseStatements)
1366         {
1367             BoundGotoCaseStatement* gotoCaseStatement = p.first;
1368             IntegralValue integralCaseValue = p.second;
1369             auto it = caseValueMap.find(integralCaseValue);
1370             if (it == caseValueMap.cend())
1371             {
1372                 throw Exception(module, "case not found", gotoCaseStatement->GetSpan());
1373             }
1374         }
1375         if (!gotoDefaultStatements.empty() && !switchStatementNode.Default())
1376         {
1377             throw Exception(module, "switch does not have a default statement", gotoDefaultStatements.front()->GetSpan());
1378         }
1379         currentGotoCaseStatements = prevGotoCaseStatements;
1380         currentGotoDefaultStatements = prevGotoDefaultStatements;
1381         currentCaseValueMap = prevCaseValueMap;
1382         if (exceptionCapture)
1383         {
1384             AddReleaseExceptionStatement(switchStatementNode.GetSpan());
1385         }
1386         AddStatement(boundSwitchStatement.release());
1387         if (switchStatementNode.Label())
1388         {
1389             statement->SetLabel(switchStatementNode.Label()->Label());
1390         }
1391         switchConditionType = prevSwitchConditionType;
1392     }
1393     else
1394     {
1395         throw Exception(module, "switch statement condition must be of integer, character, enumerated or Boolean type", switchStatementNode.Condition()->GetSpan());
1396     }
1397 }

1399 void StatementBinder::Visit(CaseStatementNode& caseStatementNode)
1400 {
1401     std::unique_ptr<BoundCaseStatement> boundCaseStatement(new BoundCaseStatement(module, caseStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1402     bool terminated = false;
1403     int n = caseStatementNode.Statements().Count();
1404     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1405     {
1406         StatementNode* statementNode = caseStatementNode.Statements()[i];
1407         if (TerminatesCase(statementNode))
1408         {
1409             terminated = true;
1410         }
1411         statementNode->Accept(*this);
1412         boundCaseStatement->AddStatement(std::move(statement));
1413     }
1414     if (!terminated)
1415     {
1416         throw Exception(module, "case must end in break, continue, return, throw, goto, goto case or goto default statement", caseStatementNode.GetSpan());
1417     }
1418     int ne = caseStatementNode.CaseExprs().Count();
1419     for (int i = 0; i < ne; ++i)
1420     {
1421         Node* caseExprNode = caseStatementNode.CaseExprs()[i];
1422         std::unique_ptr<Value> caseValue = Evaluate(caseExprNode, switchConditionType, containerScope, boundCompileUnit, false, currentFunction, caseExprNode->GetSpan());
1423         IntegralValue integralCaseValue(caseValue.get());
1424         Assert(currentCaseValueMap, "current case value map not set");
1425         auto it = currentCaseValueMap->find(integralCaseValue);
1426         if (it != currentCaseValueMap->cend())
1427         {
1428             throw Exception(module, "case value already used", caseExprNode->GetSpan());
1429         }
1430         (*currentCaseValueMap)[integralCaseValue] = &caseStatementNode;
1431         boundCaseStatement->AddCaseValue(std::move(caseValue));
1432     }
1433     AddStatement(boundCaseStatement.release());
1434     if (caseStatementNode.Label())
1435     {
1436         statement->SetLabel(caseStatementNode.Label()->Label());
1437     }
1438 }

1511 void StatementBinder::Visit(ThrowStatementNode& throwStatementNode)
1512 {
1513     bool prevCompilingThrow = compilingThrow;
1514     compilingThrow = true;
1515     if (currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->DontThrow() && !currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->HasTry())
1516     {
1517         throw Exception(module, "a nothrow function cannot contain a throw statement unless it handles exceptions", throwStatementNode.GetSpan(), currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->GetSpan());
1518     }
1519     Span span = throwStatementNode.GetSpan();
1520     Node* exceptionExprNode = throwStatementNode.Expression();
1521     if (exceptionExprNode)
1522     {
1523         std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> boundExceptionExpr = BindExpression(exceptionExprNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1524         if (boundExceptionExpr->GetType()->PlainType(span)->IsClassTypeSymbol())
1525         {
1526             ClassTypeSymbol* exceptionClassType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(boundExceptionExpr->GetType()->PlainType(span));
1527             IdentifierNode systemExceptionNode(throwStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"System.Exception");
1528             TypeSymbol* systemExceptionType = ResolveType(&systemExceptionNode, boundCompileUnit, containerScope);
1529             Assert(systemExceptionType->IsClassTypeSymbol(), "System.Exception not of class type");
1530             ClassTypeSymbol* systemExceptionClassType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(systemExceptionType);
1531             if (exceptionClassType == systemExceptionClassType || exceptionClassType->HasBaseClass(systemExceptionClassType))
1532             {
1533                 NewNode* newNode = new NewNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, exceptionClassType->FullName()));
1534                 CloneContext cloneContext;
1535                 newNode->AddArgument(throwStatementNode.Expression()->Clone(cloneContext));
1536                 InvokeNode invokeNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"RtThrowException"));
1537                 invokeNode.AddArgument(newNode);
1538                 invokeNode.AddArgument(new UuidLiteralNode(span, exceptionClassType->TypeId()));
1539                 std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> throwCallExpr = BindExpression(&invokeNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1540                 AddStatement(new BoundThrowStatement(module, span, std::move(throwCallExpr)));
1541             }
1542             else
1543             {
1544                 throw Exception(module, "exception class must be derived from System.Exception class", throwStatementNode.GetSpan());
1545             }
1546         }
1547         else
1548         {
1549             throw Exception(module, "exception not of class type", throwStatementNode.GetSpan());
1550         }
1551     }
1552     else
1553     {
1554         if (insideCatch)
1555         {
1556             InvokeNode invokeNode(span, new DotNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exPtr"), new IdentifierNode(span, U"Release")));
1557             std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> releaseCall = BindExpression(&invokeNode, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1558             AddStatement(new BoundRethrowStatement(module, span, std::move(releaseCall)));
1559         }
1560         else
1561         {
1562             throw Exception(module, "rethrow must occur inside a catch clause", throwStatementNode.GetSpan());
1563         }
1564     }
1565     if (throwStatementNode.Label())
1566     {
1567         statement->SetLabel(throwStatementNode.Label()->Label());
1568     }
1569     compilingThrow = prevCompilingThrow;
1570 }

1594 void StatementBinder::Visit(CatchNode& catchNode)
1595 {
1596     bool prevInsideCatch = insideCatch;
1597     insideCatch = true;
1598     Span span = catchNode.GetSpan();
1599     std::unique_ptr<BoundCatchStatement> boundCatchStatement(new BoundCatchStatement(module, catchNode.GetSpan()));
1600     TypeSymbol* catchedType = ResolveType(catchNode.TypeExpr(), boundCompileUnit, containerScope);
1601     boundCatchStatement->SetCatchedType(catchedType);
1602     boundCatchStatement->SetCatchedTypeUuidId(boundCompileUnit.Install(catchedType->BaseType()->TypeId()));
1603     LocalVariableSymbol* catchVar = nullptr;
1604     if (catchNode.Id())
1605     {
1606         Symbol* symbol = symbolTable.GetSymbol(catchNode.Id());
1607         Assert(symbol->GetSymbolType() == SymbolType::localVariableSymbol, "local variable symbol expected");
1608         catchVar = static_cast<LocalVariableSymbol*>(symbol);
1609         boundCatchStatement->SetCatchVar(catchVar);
1610         currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->AddLocalVariable(catchVar);
1611     }
1612     CompoundStatementNode handlerBlock(span);
1613     handlerBlock.SetEndBraceSpan(catchNode.CatchBlock()->EndBraceSpan());
1614     handlerBlock.SetParent(catchNode.Parent());
1615     ConstructionStatementNode* getExceptionAddr = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, new PointerNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"void")), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exceptionAddr"));
1616     getExceptionAddr->AddArgument(new InvokeNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"RtGetException")));
1617     handlerBlock.AddStatement(getExceptionAddr);
1618     PointerNode exceptionPtrTypeNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, catchedType->BaseType()->FullName()));
1619     CloneContext cloneContext;
1620     ConstructionStatementNode* constructExceptionPtr = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, exceptionPtrTypeNode.Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exceptionPtr"));
1621     constructExceptionPtr->AddArgument(new CastNode(span, exceptionPtrTypeNode.Clone(cloneContext), new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exceptionAddr")));
1622     handlerBlock.AddStatement(constructExceptionPtr);
1623     TemplateIdNode* uniquePtrNode = new TemplateIdNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"UniquePtr"));
1624     uniquePtrNode->AddTemplateArgument(new IdentifierNode(span, catchedType->BaseType()->FullName()));
1625     ConstructionStatementNode* constructUniquePtrException = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, uniquePtrNode, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exPtr"));
1626     constructUniquePtrException->AddArgument(new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exceptionPtr"));
1627     handlerBlock.AddStatement(constructUniquePtrException);
1628     if (catchVar)
1629     {
1630         ConstructionStatementNode* setExceptionVar = new ConstructionStatementNode(span, catchNode.TypeExpr()->Clone(cloneContext), static_cast<IdentifierNode*>(catchNode.Id()->Clone(cloneContext)));
1631         setExceptionVar->AddArgument(new DerefNode(span, new IdentifierNode(span, U"@exPtr")));
1632         handlerBlock.AddStatement(setExceptionVar);
1633     }
1634     handlerBlock.AddStatement(static_cast<StatementNode*>(catchNode.CatchBlock()->Clone(cloneContext)));
1635     symbolTable.BeginContainer(containerScope->Container());
1636     SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreatorVisitor(symbolTable);
1637     handlerBlock.Accept(symbolCreatorVisitor);
1638     symbolTable.EndContainer();
1639     TypeBinder typeBinder(boundCompileUnit);
1640     typeBinder.SetContainerScope(containerScope);
1641     typeBinder.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
1642     handlerBlock.Accept(typeBinder);
1643     handlerBlock.Accept(*this);
1644     boundCatchStatement->SetCatchBlock(std::move(statement));
1645     AddStatement(boundCatchStatement.release());
1646     insideCatch = prevInsideCatch;
1647 }

1649 void StatementBinder::Visit(AssertStatementNode& assertStatementNode)
1650 {
1651     if (!module)
1652     {
1653         throw std::runtime_error("module not set");
1654     }
1655     bool unitTesting = GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest) && InUnitTest();
1656     bool unitTestAssertion = false;
1657     if (unitTesting)
1658     {
1659         FunctionSymbol* functionSymbol = currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol();
1660         Node* node = symbolTable.GetNodeNoThrow(functionSymbol);
1661         if (node)
1662         {
1663             if (node->GetNodeType() == NodeType::functionNode)
1664             {
1665                 FunctionNode* functionNode = static_cast<FunctionNode*>(node);
1666                 if ((functionNode->GetSpecifiers() & Specifiers::unit_test_) != Specifiers::none)
1667                 {
1668                     unitTestAssertion = true;
1669                 }
1670             }
1671         }
1672     }
1673     if (unitTestAssertion)
1674     {
1675         int32_t assertionLineNumber = assertStatementNode.GetSpan().LineNumber();
1676         int32_t assertionIndex = GetNextUnitTestAssertionNumber();
1677         AddAssertionLineNumber(assertionLineNumber);
1678         InvokeNode* invokeSetUnitTestAssertionResult = new InvokeNode(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), new IdentifierNode(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), U"RtSetUnitTestAssertionResult"));
1679         invokeSetUnitTestAssertionResult->AddArgument(new IntLiteralNode(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), assertionIndex));
1680         CloneContext cloneContext;
1681         invokeSetUnitTestAssertionResult->AddArgument(assertStatementNode.AssertExpr()->Clone(cloneContext));
1682         invokeSetUnitTestAssertionResult->AddArgument(new IntLiteralNode(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), assertionLineNumber));
1683         ExpressionStatementNode setUnitTestAssertionResult(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), invokeSetUnitTestAssertionResult);
1684         symbolTable.BeginContainer(containerScope->Container());
1685         SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreatorVisitor(symbolTable);
1686         setUnitTestAssertionResult.Accept(symbolCreatorVisitor);
1687         symbolTable.EndContainer();
1688         TypeBinder typeBinder(boundCompileUnit);
1689         typeBinder.SetContainerScope(containerScope);
1690         typeBinder.SetCurrentFunctionSymbol(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol());
1691         setUnitTestAssertionResult.Accept(typeBinder);
1692         setUnitTestAssertionResult.Accept(*this);
1693     }
1694     else
1695     {
1696         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::release))
1697         {
1698             AddStatement(new BoundEmptyStatement(module, assertStatementNode.GetSpan()));
1699         }
1700         else
1701         {
1702             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> lookups;
1703             lookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, symbolTable.GlobalNs().GetContainerScope()));
1704             std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> arguments;
1705             TypeSymbol* constCharPtrType = symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"char")->AddConst(assertStatementNode.GetSpan())->AddPointer(assertStatementNode.GetSpan());
1706             arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLiteral(module, std::unique_ptr<Value>(new StringValue(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), 
1707                 boundCompileUnit.Install(assertStatementNode.AssertExpr()->ToString()))), constCharPtrType)));
1708             arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLiteral(module, std::unique_ptr<Value>(new StringValue(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), 
1709                 boundCompileUnit.Install(ToUtf8(currentFunction->GetFunctionSymbol()->FullName())))), constCharPtrType)));
1710             arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLiteral(module, std::unique_ptr<Value>(new StringValue(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), 
1711                 boundCompileUnit.Install(module->GetFilePath(assertStatementNode.GetSpan().FileIndex())))), constCharPtrType)));
1712             arguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundLiteral(module, std::unique_ptr<Value>(new IntValue(assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), 
1713                 assertStatementNode.GetSpan().LineNumber())), symbolTable.GetTypeByName(U"int"))));
1714             std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression> assertExpression = BindExpression(assertStatementNode.AssertExpr(), boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, containerScope, this);
1715             std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement> ifStatement(new BoundIfStatement(module, assertStatementNode.GetSpan(), std::move(assertExpression), 
1716                      std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundEmptyStatement(module, assertStatementNode.GetSpan())), 
1717                      std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, ResolveOverload(U"RtFailAssertion", containerScope, lookups, arguments, boundCompileUnit, currentFunction, 
1718                     assertStatementNode.GetSpan())))));
1719             AddStatement(ifStatement.release());
1720         }
1721     }
1722 }

1729 void StatementBinder::Visit(ConditionalCompilationDisjunctionNode& conditionalCompilationDisjunctionNode)
1730 {

1733     conditionalCompilationStack.pop();
